\sin x
\int\delta'(x)\cos x\ dx = \delta(x)
\int\delta'(x)\sin x \ dx  = \delta(x)\sin x - \int\delta(x)\cos x\ dx = 0 - \theta(x) = -\theta(x),
u(x) = \theta(x)\cos x
